Q6. Given an array arr, rotate the array by one position in clockwise direction.
    Examples:
    Input: arr[] = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]
    Output: [5, 1, 2, 3, 4]
    Explanation: If we rotate arr by one position in clockwise 5 come to the front and 
    remaining those are shifted to the end.

Sol(6)- class Solution{
        public void rotate(int[] arr){
            int temp = arr[arr.length-1];
            for(int i = arr.length-1; i >0; i--){
                arr[i] = arr[i-1];
            }
            arr[0] = temp;
        
           }
        }



